nickname meaning

hi little, first of all, congrats on crossing!!! Iâm so proud of u for pushing through until the end â and you deserve it.
so your nickname is tiramisu, and i chose this nickname for you because of several different reasons. 

[connection to my family line]

first of all, I wanted to give you a nickname related to my family line. 
as you may know, tiramisu is composed of coffee, creme, and alcohol, all of which are directly related to me (mocha), my big (Bailey), and my gbig (creme). as your ingredients, I wanted your nickname to serve you as a reminder that we are all here to support you no matter what. 

as much as you remind me of myself, you also resemble my big in so many ways â as you know - u, me and my big - we all have the same exact mbti. and like you said, I canât help but think that âthis is fate.â

maybe thatâs why weâve all been procrastinating to schedule a meet up with all three of us â but I assure you, my big has been looking forward to meeting you before I even picked you up, and weâll make that happen before the end of this semester.

other than that, cream is an ingredient that blend in well with almost any dessert, 
just like how you get along with almost everyone, and alcohol adds spice to the flavor just like how you make everyone laugh with your spicy humor. 

[our dynamic]
secondly, tiramisu and coffee are the perfect pair just like we are.

Coffee changes the texture of the ladyfinger sponges in tiramisu, and this is similar to how I aspire to be a big sister figure that you can rely on. I aspire to be the person you can reach out to for any guidance give you and the person that you can rant to without any worries.

Also, coffee functions as a balance to the sweetness of the cream in tiramisu. Whenever I talk to you, especially regarding relationships, i noticed that youâre exceptionally wise and mature for people of your age. I see you not only also a cute little sister but also a reliable friend figure. The day when I was going through a rough time and you pulled over to kdphi house, I was truly comforted by your presence and words. I think you are better than me at handling relationships.

you can be so humorous but grounded and down to earth at the same time. like tiramisu, you are sweet, rich in flavor, a bit fragile, and warm and cozy. 

[Ciciâs qualities]

In Italian, tiramisu means âcheer me upâ and holds a reference to its caffeine-containing ingredients, which is coffee.

Iâm usually very hesitant to reach out first, but your bright smile broke my barriers down. I actually think that you are the first person Iâve reached out to in my life.  

just like a bite of tiramisu, you increase my energy levels, help me feel less tired, and boost my mood. on my lowest days, simply talking to you gives me the small rush of endorphins i need, and makes me feel so much better.

Just like tiramisu is one of the most widely known and loved desserts on the planet, I know that you will continue to be loved by more and more people around you. I genuinely admire all of your qualities, and I hope this name fills your life with even more love through the connections you make in and outside of kdphi. I am so so proud to have you as my little, and I love you with all my heart.

If you ask questions during the test, I may not be able to answer right then, but I will answer after weâre done. Finally, please think out loud as you go through the tasks. 

Iâm going to demonstrate a process for thinking out loud. For example, we are currently on Zaraâs website, and our goal is to shop for womenâs jeans.
